<HEADLINE> Shanghai Edges Shandong to Rise to 2nd Place </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Oriental edged
Shandong Flaming Bulls 65-62 in Shanghai to rise to the second
place of the Chinese Men's Basketball First Division on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, entering Sunday's 10th round with seven wins and two
losses same as Shandong, rallied from a 4-0 deficit at the
beginning to lead 34-27 before the break.
</P>
<P>
Shandong staged a comeback in the second half and levelled the
score at 62-62 after hitting three consecutive three-pointers.
</P>
<P>
With 16 seconds remaining, a decisive lay-up by Liang Da put
Shanghai ahead and an ensuing free-throw sealed the host's
victory.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, with eight wins and two losses, now stands second on
the standings behind Army Rockets, which defeated Beijing Ducks in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Liu Yudong of Rockets hit 25 of his 30 points in the first half
of the 114-82 victory to maintain their lead with a nine-win and
one-loss record.
</P>
<P>
The Army Rockets, who lost their first game since October in
1993 to the Liaoning Hunters last Wednesday on the home court of
Xi'an, never faced the challenge and took a 58-39 halftime lead.
</P>
<P>
Liu Yudong also contributed eight rebounds in his 23 minutes
play for the defending champions, which extended the lead to
87-52, the larggest margin in the game, with 11 minutes left.
</P>
<P>
Liu Qiang added 22 points for the Army team, which had three
other players to score a double-figure pionts with Li Nan's 17,
Zhang Jingsong's 15 and Wang Sheng's 10.
</P>
<P>
Bateer led the Ducks with a game-high 32 points in his 40
minutes performance. Liu Hongwei scored 16 points for Beijing,
which had a 4-6 record to be a lowly 7th in the league.
</P>
<P>
Also on Sunday, Liaoning Hunters defeated Guangdong Tigers
84-78 in Dongguan, Guangdong Province, to place third in the
league, while Tigers were fourth.
</P>
<P>
In the other matches, Sichuan Pandas downed Zhejiang Squirrels
78-71 in Chengdu, Sichuan Province, Jiangsu Nangang beat Jinan
Pegasus 108-94 in Nanjing, Jiangsu Province, and Lianhang Eagles
vanquished Shenyang Lions 81-77 in Baoding, Hebei Province.
</P>
</TEXT>
