<HEADLINE> Rebels Kill 3 in Southwestern Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Remnants of Allied Democratic
Forces (ADF) rebels have killed three people while terrorizing
villagers in Kasese district, southwestern Uganda.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here today said hundreds of people left
their villages and went to towns on Friday where government
soldiers have detachments.
</P>
<P>
The fleeing civilians were quoted as saying rebels attacked
the area at about 9:00 p.m. that day and also stole goats,
chickens and dried beans, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of people have also been displaced following the
incidents in the area, the report added.
</P>
<P>
Security officials were quoted as saying that government
troops immediately pursued the rebels after the incidents.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
