<HEADLINE> Greek Cargo Ship Capasizes in Aegean </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Athens, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Twenty people are missing after
a Greek cargo ship capsized in bad weather in the Aegean Saturday,
the country's Merchant Marine Ministry said today.
</P>
<P>
Navy, coast guard, helicopters and other rescue crews are
searching the area, but so far only one crew member has been
rescued.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said in a statement that hopes are looking dim
that the remaining missing, 17 men, two women and a ten-year-old
girl who were aboard the ship, will be found.
</P>
<P>
The ship Distos, owned by the Greece' Heracles Cement Company,
capsized off the port of Kini on island of Evia late Saturday
night. It was carrying 5,300 tons of cement from Volos in central
Greece to Piraeu, an adjacent port city of Athens. 
</P>
</TEXT>
