<HEADLINE> Jordan Keen on Activating Financial Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian Prime Minister Abdul
Karim Kabariti stressed here today that Jordan was keen to
activate the Amman financial market (AFM), the local press
reported.
</P>
<P>
The role of the AFM would be energized after the government
endorsed a package of economic legislation related to companies,
banknotes, customs and the rights of intellectual properties,
Kabariti said.
</P>
<P>
Those important issues would be discussed in the current
parliamentary session, said the prime minister while addressing
the visitors to AFM.
</P>
<P>
Laws would play positive and effective role in developing
Jordan's national economy, he said.
</P>
<P>
According to a study, the AFM is poised to be one of the
cheapest stock exchanges in the world next year.
</P>
<P>
This is due to the expected improvement in the performance of
the large companies by no less than 25 percent rise from that in
1996, the study said. The improvement resulted from the
endorsement of a new package of economic laws, especially those
about lower income taxes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
