<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Africa Beats Germany in Hopman Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 30 (Xinhua) -- South Africa beat Germany 3-0
in their opening match of the Hopman Cup mixed team tennis
tournament in Perth, Australia, on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Amanda Coetzer overwhelmed Petra Begerow 6-0, 7-5 in the
women's singles while Wayne Ferreira defeated Bernd Karbacher 6-4,
6-4 in the men's singles on the second day of the eight-nation
tournament.
</P>
<P>
South Africa also won the "dead" mixed doubles 6-3, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
In the first clash of the day, Switzerland overcame heavy odds
to defeat Romania 2-1.
</P>
<P>
Troubled by a painful back, Swiss giant Marc Rosset decided to
withdraw from the men's singles against Adrian Voinea.
</P>
<P>
After his compatriot Martina Hingis beat Irina Spirlea 7-5, 6-2
in the women's singles, Rosset paired up with Hingis to defeat
Voinea and Spirlea 3-6, 7-5, 6-3 in the doubles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
