<HEADLINE> Cyprus Soccer Body Meet on Match-Fixing Claims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The Cyprus Football
Association met on Monday to discuss the probe into allegations of
match rigging in a World Cup qualifier against Bulgaria earlier
this month.
</P>
<P>
Members of the federation are expected to ask for police
intervention in the investigation of claims that national team
players placed heavy bets on losing to Bulgaria. Cyprus lost 3-1
to Bulgaria in Limassol on December 14.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus Football Association vice chairman Costas Koutsokoumnis
told the parliament that usually around 3,000 pounds (6,400
U.S. dollars) is placed on such games but 30,000 pounds was placed
in bets for the Cyprus-Bulgaria match.
</P>
<P>
The soccer body is calling for a ban on all betting involving
national teams and local teams, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
