<HEADLINE> First Foreign Banks to Do RMB Business In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 30 (Xinhua) -- City Bank NA, the Hong Kong
and Shanghai Bank, the Bank of Tokyo - Mitsubishi, and the
Industrial Bank of Japan have become the first foreign banks to do
business in RMB yuan in China.
</P>
<P>
The four banks have been permitted to move their Shanghai
branches to the Pudong New Area and to start handling Chinese
currency business there, according to officials at the People's
Bank of China Shanghai Branch.
</P>
<P>
They have also been allowed to keep their downtown Shanghai
branches, but only for foreign exchange business.
</P>
<P>
Since the People's Bank of China (PBC) issued provisional rules
on foreign banks doing business in Renminbi yuan on December 12,
the Shanghai branch of the country's central bank has been busy
handling applications submitted by foreign banks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
