<HEADLINE> Slovenia Keeps World Cup Races </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVE, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Two men's Alpine skiing World
Cup races which were in doubt for January 5 and 6 in Kranjska Gora
will proceed as scheduled, the International Ski Federation (FIS)
said in Oberhofen, Switzerland, on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The FIS had given the organisers until Monday to determine if
conditions would allow the Slovenian resort to stage the first two
men's races of the new year - a slalom and a giant slalom - or
risk losing them to Veysonnaz, Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
The FIS also said a women's downhill originally scheduled for
December 20 in Crans Montana, Switzerland, but postponed because
of soft snow would be added to the programme in Bad
Kleinkirchheim, Austria.
</P>
<P>
The race will be the first of back-to-back downhills on
January 10 and 11 followed by a super giant slalom on January 12.
</P>
</TEXT>
