<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lu Ping Confident About Hong Kong's Future (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He said the formation of the Provisional Legislative Council
was an important component part of the preparatory work for the
SAR, and received the support of the vast majority of the people
of Hong Kong, and the 60 Council members come from various sectors
of Hong Kong society and have a wide representation.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the Preparatory Committee will live up to the
expectations of the people, including Hong Kong compatriots, and
has fulfiled its tasks and provided an important guarantee for a
smooth transition, he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
In referring to how the SAR government will be formed, Lu said
that, according to the Basic Law, principal officials of the SAR
will be nominated by the Chief Executive, who will report on this
to the Central People's Government for approval.
</P>
<P>
These principal officials will shoulder the historic task of
helping with a smooth transition and building a prosperous Hong
Kong, he said, noting that they must pledge their loyalty to the
Hong Kong SAR government of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
This reflects the principle of "Hong Kong people governing Hong
Kong" and the high-degree autonomy, he added, saying that it is up
to the Chief Executive to consider forming the SAR government, and
the central government has full faith in this.
</P>
<P>
The central government places great hopes in the HK SAR
government-designate and is convinced that, with the support of
the people of Hong Kong, they will provide a new historical
chapter for the Hong Kong SAR, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
