<HEADLINE> HongkongBank to Conduct Renminbi Business in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The Hongkong and Shanghai
Banking Corporation Ltd. (HongkongBank) has got approval from the
People's Bank of China to set up a new branch in Pudong and
conduct renminbi business in Shanghai, HongkongBank said here
today.
</P>
<P>
The branch in Pudong will become the bank's main branch in
Shanghai, offering, in addition to the approved renminbi business,
 a full range of banking facilities in foreign currencies, as well
 as trade-related finance and other banking services. It will be
supported by a subbranch operating in Puxi.
</P>
<P>
Chris Langley, general manager for Hong Kong and China, said,
"We are very pleased with these latest developments in China. The
license to conduct Renminbi business is a major step forward in
China's financial reform and is welcomed by HongkongBank which is
committed to retaining its status as the leading foreign bank in
China."
</P>
<P>
In addition to Shanghai, HongkongBank has five other branches
in China, located in Beijing, Qingdao, Shenzhen, Tianjin and
Xiamen. The bank also has four representative offices in Chengdu,
Dalian, Guangzhou and Wuhan. Approval, however, has recently been
given to upgrade the representative office in Dalian to a branch.
</P>
<P>
HongkongBank, together with its subsidiaries, has nearly 600
offices in 20 Asian countries. It is a principal member of the
HSBC Group which, with more than 3,400 offices in 77 countries and
assets in excess of 400 billion U.S. dollars, is among the world's
largest banking and financial services institutions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
