<HEADLINE> Program-Controlled Switch Makers Unify Targets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- China's manufacturers of
program-controlled telephone switching machine have reached an
agreement to coordinate their development and set a common
technical standard.
</P>
<P>
According to the Beijing-based "People's Posts and
Telecommunications News," since January 1, 1997, all the country's
makers of the 04 switch gear, the first large-capacity
program-controlled switching system developed by Chinese
scientists, will readjust their development pace and abide by a
set of agreements on producing scale, component supply, trademark,
market strategies, quality control, post-sale service and
technical renovation.
</P>
<P>
The Great Dragon Telecom Co (GDT)., a national-level industrial
company which was jointly funded by China's eight producers of 04
switches, will serve as the sole agent for the 04 machines both on
domestic and overseas markets.
</P>
<P>
The 04 machine has led the sales of domestic switches for five
years. By the end of October, some eight million lines of 04
machines were sold in the country, covering 28 provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions.
</P>
<P>
GDT's unifications drive is viewed by local analysts as a new
strategy for the Chinese telecom industry to break the monopoly of
foreign products on the switching machine market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
