<HEADLINE> Taiwan Products Center to Be Inaugurated in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Businessmen from Taiwan and
Macao will jointly launch a Taiwan Products Center in Macao,
aiming to pave the way for the entry of Taiwan products to the
mainland market.
</P>
<P>
The Taiwan Products Center, scheduled to be inaugurated here
Tuesday and to offer thousands of kinds of Taiwan products, is the
first of its kind in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Jose Cheong Vai Chi, president of the center, said the center
costs a combined investment of 30 million Hong Kong dollars (about
3.88 million U.S. dollars), with half from local investors and
half from Taiwan investors.
</P>
<P>
The center is only a starting point in promoting trade between
Taiwan and the mainland, said Chi, who has contacted local
businessmen in Guangzhou, Zhuhai and Zhongshan cities in south
China's Guangdong Province for plans to expand shop chains to
those places.
</P>
<P>
"We can also be a 'matchmaker' in promoting mainland products
to Taiwan. We can reprocess mainland products here in Macao and
then re-export them to Taiwan," he said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed an optimistic view on trade between the mainland
and Taiwan, saying it would be the center's main source of
profits.
</P>
<P>
The center will initially deal with foodstuffs and household
appliances, plus computers, arts and crafts, brand-name fashion
and sportswear. It plans to expand its business scope to more than
20,000 kinds in the future, said Chi.  
</P>
</TEXT>
