<HEADLINE> HK Restaurants' Receipts Increase in 3rd Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The value of total receipts
for Hong Kong's restaurants sector in the third quarter of 1996
increased by 6 percent over the same quarter in 1995 to 14 billion
HK dollars (1.79 billion US dollars), according to the provisional
figures released today by the Census and Statistics Department.
</P>
<P>
The value of total purchase of restaurants also increased by 6
percent to 5 billion HK dollars (641 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
After discounting the effect of price changes over the period,
total restaurant receipts increased slightly by 2 percent in
volume terms.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the Census and Statistics Department said here
today it is the first time when positive year-on-year growth in
volume terms has been registered since the first quarter of 1994.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that compared with a year ago, total
receipts of all types of restaurants registered increases in both
value and volume terms.
</P>
<P>
Among them, non-Chinese food restaurants and fast food shops
had the most rapid growth, both showing an upsurge of 10 percent
in value terms.
</P>
<P>
In volume terms, their total receipts rose by 6 percent and 4
percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The total receipts of miscellaneous eating and drinking places
recorded an increase of 9 percent in value and 4 percent in
volume.
</P>
<P>
Total receipts of bars and Chinese restaurants also went up, by
8 percent and 3 percent in value respectively. In volume terms,
both of them recorded a marginal growth of 1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Comparing with the preceding quarter, total receipts for the
restaurants sector in the third quarter of 1996 increased by 8
percent in value and 7 percent in volume.
</P>
<P>
Comparing the first three quarters of 1996 with the same
period of 1995, total restaurant receipts rose by 4 percent in
value, but showed virtually no change in volume.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
