opened early this year. Several boys and girls from foreign
countries are getting along very well with the local children at
the school. The school owner, Mary Chongo herself prepares lunch
for the children who have come from families of government
officials, businessmen, doctors, workers and individual laborers.
</P>
<P>
Of them, the yongest is only 15 months and the oldest six
years old. Some stay here in the morning and some the whole day.
The half-day care costs 150,000 Kwacha (about 115 U.S.Dollars)
and the all-day care costs 200,000 Kwacha (154 Dollars) for three
months. Middle-class families can afford to send their children
to the school, Chongo said.
</P>
<P>
In lusaka, there are many private nursery schools like this.
Generally speaking, the private schools provide much better
education and accommodations than those run by city councils.
</P>
<P>
Parents send their children to the expensive private schools
to enable children having access to a better pre-school education
before their childern go to primary shools.
</P>
<P>
In Longacres School Curriculum includes English, mathematics,
music, painting, sanitary, environmental and social science and
Creative activities. The curriculum aims at providing the
children with opportunities and experience necessary for the
development of mental, physical and emotional, spiritual and
moral abilities and potentialities.
</P>
<P>
The Children have been divided into different age groups to
perform activities suitable for them under a national pre-school
syllabus.
</P>
<P>
Zambia has attached importance to the pre-school education.
The Zambia Pre-School Association (ZPA),since its formation in
1972, has opened workshops to train teachers for pre-school
education in both rural and urban communities. A two-year
pre-school teachers course is now going on at David Livingstone
Teachers Training College and Kitwe Teachers Training College.
</P>
</TEXT>
