<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Plans to Export 108,000 Tons of Coffee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The Coffee and Tea
Authority of Ethiopia has announced that it would earn 236
million dollars from the export of 108,000 tons of coffee in the
1996-97 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
General Manager of the authority Tsegaye Birhane told the
local press that the plan is the highest ever in the coffee
export history of the country and six percent more than the
figure exported in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
He said the country has already earned 92 million dollars from
the sale in the world market of 36,907 tons of coffee in the
first five months of this fiscal year, which starts on July 8,
1996, and ends on July 7, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The decline in coffee prices on the world market makes the
decrease of earning for Ethiopia from coffee export in recent
eyars. Ethiopia earned 279.5 million dollars from the sale of
102,000 tons of coffee in 1995-96 and 287.8 million dollars from
exporting 78,420 tons of coffee in 1994-95.
</P>
<P>
Coffee is the source of more than half of the country's hard
currency earnings. About 25 percent of the Ethiopians are engaged
in coffee production, trade or related activities directly or
indirectly. enditem

