<HEADLINE> CPPCC Vice-Chairman Offers Condolence on Death of Vietnamese leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) --Wang Zhaoguo, vice-chairman of
the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference, expressed his condolence on the death of
Nguyen Huu Tho, honorary chairman of the Central Committee of the
Fatherland Front of Vietnam, at the Vietnamese embassy in China
today.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi, chairman of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress, Li Ruihuan, chairman of the CPPCC National
Committee, and Rong Yiren, Chinese vice-president, presented
wreathes to the embassy.
</P>
<P>
Nguyen died at the age of 86 in Ho Chi Minh city on December
24.
</P>
<P>
CPPCC Chairman Li Ruihuan sent a message of condolence to
Vietnamese Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet on the death of Nguyen.
</P>
<P>
Nguyen, a prominent leader of Vietnam, once took the posts as
Chairman of the Presidium of the Central Committee of the National
Liberation Front of south Vietnam, president of the Council of
State of Vietnam, and Acting Vietnamese President.
</P>
<P>
Also at the Vietnamese embassy today to offer condolences on
Nguyen's death were Tang Jiaxuan, vice-foreign minister; Qi
Huaiyuan, president of the Chinese People's Association for
Friendship with foreign Countries; and ranking officials from
relevant departments. 
</P>
