<HEADLINE> Tung Chee Hwa Meets with HK Provisional Legislators </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive designate of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) Tung Chee Hwa today
met with 48 members of the Provisional Legislative Council (PLC)
of the HKSAR and held informal discussions with them.
</P>
<P>
Tung said at a press briefing afterwards that the purposes of
the meeting were to congratulate them on their success in becoming
members of the PLC and to discuss very unofficially what was the
road ahead like.
</P>
<P>
"I thought it was a very useful discussion," he said. "I told
them their work is very important and I wish them success."
</P>
<P>
He said the PLC has much work to do and should hold its first
meeting as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
He stressed again the importance of civil servants' political
neutrality.
</P>
<P>
"We must respect civil servants' political neutrality, and in
fact they will maintain their neutrality," he added.
</P>
<P>
The PLC elected on December 21 has 60 members, some of whom are
presently not in Hong Kong. 
