<HEADLINE> China, Sudan to Cooperate in Petroleum Exploitation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice Premier Wu
Bangguo said here today that China wished to promote its
cooperation with Sudan in exploiting petroleum and natural gas
on the principle of mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks today during a meeting with Sudanese
Minister of Energy and Mines Awed Ahmed Al-Jaz.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that China valued its relations with Sudan, and that
both were developing countries and faced with the similar problem
of economic development.
</P>
<P>
Ahmed Al-Jaz asked the vice premier to forward a letter from
Sudanese President El-Bashir to President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
He said that Sudan and China had been engaged in cooperation in
many areas including petroleum and natural gas, sugar industry,
and agricultural machinery.The Sudanese government had given its
approval of such cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed the hope that the cooperation in the field of
petroleum would deepen the bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the two sides also exchanged views on
issues of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
The Sudanese guests arrived in Beijing last Friday as guests of
the China National Petroleum Corporation. 
</P>
