<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rise on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Share prices rose on the
Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index
gained 15.85 points to close at 2,218.45 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was very thin at 51.77 million units,
worth 143.06 million Singapore dollars (about 102.19 million US
dollars). Advances overwhelmed declines 198 to 76, while 317 other
counters stayed steady.
</P>
<P>
Kim Eng warrant97 was the most actively traded counter as it
posted a turnover of 4.67 million units. It was followed by
Uniphoenix which had 4.25 million shares traded. Nobel Des was
next with 1.75 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 and the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign
shared the top spot on the gainers' list as each of them advanced
by 70 cents to finish at 14.1 and 27.5 Singapore dollars
respectively. The Overseas Chinese Banking Corporation (OCBC)
Foreign rose by 50 cents to 17.4 Singapore dollars, while CMSPort
was 45 cents higher at 5.55 Hong Kong dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Chem Ind was the biggest loser as it declined
by 28 cents to end at 3.2 dollars. The Singapore Airlines lost 20
cents to close at 12.6 Singapore dollars, while TAC 200 was 15
cents lower at 6.8 US dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
