<DOCNO> XIE19961230.0101 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Legislature Ends Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Legislature, the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC),
approved the Hong Kong Garrison Law and several important
decisions today.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi, chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, presided over
the closure of the 23rd session of the Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
With a decree signed by President Jiang Zemin, the Hong Kong
Garrison Law will take effect on July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Several changes were made to the draft before put for vote this
afternoon according to opinions of the lawmakers. The revisions
were to protect the interests of all the people in Hong Kong, and
further discipline the military personnel to be stationed there.
</P>
<P>
The draft law on administrative supervision, which was proposed
for adoption at this meeting, was eventually withdrawn from voting
because legislators sharply disagreed with the name of the law,
according to Qiao, who explained to the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Some believed that it should be named as the law on
administrative supervision according to what the law
regulates. But others said according to Constitutional concepts,
it was more proper to be named as the law on supervision.
</P>
<P>
Qiao suggested that the issue to be further discussed and put
for a vote on the next Standing Committee session to be held in
next February. His suggestion was based on a conclusion of a
meeting attended by vice-chairmen of the NPC Standing Committee
just before the closing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Qiao's proposal was adopted by the meeting today.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also decided to present the draft National Defense
Law to the 5th plenum of the Eight NPC for approval. Also to be
discussed at that meeting were two decisions, one on the election of
the deputies to the Ninth NPC (1998--2003), another on the
election of Hong Kong deputies to the Ninth NPC in particular.
</P>
<P>
According to another resolution approved today, the Fifth
Session of the Eighth NPC will be convoked on March 1, next year,
in which a number of important political, economic and social
matters will be examined.
</P>
<P>
Also approved were two international conventions, respectively
on control of desertification in countries with sever drought
and/or desertification and especially in Africa and on prohibition
of the development, production, stockpiling and use of chemical
weapons and on their destruction as well as a treaty concerning
boundary between China and Kirghistan.
</P>
<P>
The legislature also approved the appointment of Cao Gangchuan
to replace Ding Henggao as Minister in Charge of the Commission of
Sciences, Technology and Industry for National Defense.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin signed a decree today to publish the
replacement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19961230.0102 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qian on Relations With Surrounding Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- China has scored new progress
in its relations with neighboring countries this year, Chinese
Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen said here today.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, he noted that Chinese President
Jiang Zemin visited three South Asian nations and the Philippines
in 1996. The trips were successful, Qian said, and is an important
diplomatic move for consolidating the peaceful environment around
China.
</P>
<P>
China and these four countries have determined the 21st
century-oriented path of development, Qian said, adding that China
and India signed an important agreement aimed at strengthening
mutual trust. And for the first time, China explained,
comprehensively and systematically, its policy toward south Asia,
the Chinese foreign minister said.
</P>
<P>
Also this year, Chinese Premier Li Peng attended the Eighth
Congress of the Communist Party of Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
During 1996, Chinese leaders visited the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea, Vietnam, Thailand, Malaysia, Indonesia and the
Republic of Korea -- all trips deepened mutual understanding,
enhanced friendship and expanded cooperation between China and
these countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
China also became a dialoque partner of the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) this year, and the relations
between the two sides advanced to a new step, Qian noted.
</P>
<P>
In addition to advancing economic and trade relations with its
neighboring countries, China has also explored new ways to expand
economic exchanges, such as making full use of non-governmental
organizations and capital, and increasing economic and trade
cooperation with its small and medium-sized neighboring nations,
the foreign minister said.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that all of these efforts have created a fine basis
and impetus to promote the overall development of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
China has carried out multi-faceted security dialogue and
cooperation, Qian said, and China's position on settling disputes
through peaceful negotiations has been well received from other
nations.
</P>
<P>
During Chinese President's visit to the Philippines, the two
sides agreed to set aside differences and engage in joint
exploration, and this will greatly benefit the peaceful settlement
of the Nansha question, Qian pointed out.
</P>
<P>
China has also actively participated in regional political and
security discussions and cooperation, including the ASEAN forum,
which has deepened mutual trust and understanding between China
and its neighboring countries, and has contributed to peace and
stability in the region, Qian said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19961230.0103 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Preparing for Railway Transport Peak over Spring Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Railways will
add a total of 111 trains to accommodate China's annual
transportation blitz during the Spring Festival -- the Chinese
Lunar New Year -- which falls on February 7, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Included are 45 long-distance trains and 66 trains for medium
and short journeys, with a total of 4,640 cars, according to Yao
Jinzhu, an official of the Transportation Department of the
Ministry of Railways.
</P>
<P>
The transport peak will last for 50 days, from January 18 to
March 8. It is estimated that trains will carry 133 million
travelers during the period, a slight drop over 1996, and the
number of long-distance passengers will reach 29.3 million, up 4.6
percent, she said.
</P>
<P>
New rail lines, especially the Beijing-Kowloon railway, will
have much more train travelers during the Spring Festival,
Yao said.
</P>
<P>
The ministry is also taking into consideration the fact that
some areas struck by severe flooding this year will receive a
greater influx of travelers, mostly former residents there who
were displaced and are returning home for the holidays, the
official said.
</P>
<P>
Ticket prices will not be raised during the festival, Yao
said. The Ministry of Railways will place emphasis on passenger
transport on 11 trunk lines, including Beijing-Guangzhou,
Beijing-Shanghai, and Beijing-Harbin railways, and lengthen the
service section of ten pairs of long-distance trains, Yao said.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the ministry will put into temporary
service 17 pairs of passenger trains, which have been added to a
new rail schedule to become operational next April 1.
</P>
<P>
No boxcars will be used during the Spring Festival, she said,
adding that efforts will be made to increase the number of ticket
offices, expand the use of computerized ticketing systems, and
lengthen periods for ticket booking.
</P>
<P>
She said that priority will be given to transport college
students who will return home during the winter holiday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19961230.0104 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qian on Sino-EU Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Developing long-term and
stable cooperative relations between China and the European Union
not only serves the interest of both sides, but also will
contribute to world peace, stability and development.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen made the
comment today in an interview with Xinhua. He said that there have
been frequent high-level exchanges of visit between China and some
members of the European Union this year.
</P>
<P>
The EU is China's fourth largest trade partner, and one of the
country's main cooperative partners in the fields of investment
and technology, he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that bilateral cooperation in scientific,
technological, cultural and educational fields has also been
expanded.
</P>
<P>
In December 1995, the European Commission approved a long-term
policy on Sino-European relations. One month ago, the commission
adopted a new Strategy towards China, which is more specific and
further stresses its comprehensive, independent and long-term
policy towards China, Qian said.
</P>
<P>
China welcomes all this, he added.
</P>
<P>
However, the two sides have different views on certain
questions, and there still exist some problems in their bilateral
ties which cannot be neglected, he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
China hopes that the EU will cancel its trade protection
measures against China's exports, in order to benefit the smooth
development of bilateral trade, Qian noted.
</P>
<P>
As long as the two sides abide by the principles of mutual
respect, seeking common ground while reserving differences,
non-interference into each other's internal affairs and equality
and mutual benefit, China-EU relations can continue to grow
steadily, Qian said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19961230.0105 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas Fund Prepares to Enter China's Retail Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- A development fund registered
in the Cayman Islands is seeking partners to break into the huge
Chinese retail market.
</P>
<P>
The new "China Commerce Development Fund" involves a total
registered capital of 167.5 million US dollars from the American
International Group of the United States, as well as several
companies from Europe and Asia.
</P>
<P>
The fund's managers are looking for powerful overseas retail
developers to be their technical partners, and large Chinese
state-owned commercial enterprises to serve as their business
partners to help tap into the Chinese market, sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government's relevant policies and project approval
procedures will be strictly observed, the sources noted.
</P>
<P>
The response of the Chinese commercial sector to the fund has
been positive.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that the main purpose of opening up the retail
market is to promote the modernization of Chinese retail
enterprises and boost the market.
</P>
<P>
And since the retail market is diverse, including department
stores, supermarket and commodity distribution centers, it is
necessary to offer guidance to overseas investors to help them
invest wisely. The special fund makes it easier to do just that,
the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Chinese experts also pointed out that the fund also reflects
the growing interest of overseas investors in China's retail
market.
</P>
<P>
Chinese government leaders and high-ranking officials in charge
of the commercial sector have on many occasions this year expressed
the willingness to open up the retail market still wider.
</P>
<P>
Eleven cities are now experimenting with the opening-up of the
retail market, and officials are considering ways to increase the
number, and to open the wholesale market to overseas
developers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19961230.0106 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xi'an Improves Environment Appeals To Overseas Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, December 30 (Xinhua)-- Xi'an, the capital of Shaanxi
Province in northwest China, has approved 125 overseas-funded
enterprises involving 370 million US dollars this year.
</P>
<P>
A city official attributed the good result to the improvement
of investment conditions.
</P>
<P>
The 3,100-year-old city has built a second south-east ring
road, and laid underground natural gas pipelines. It has also
diverted water from the Heihe and Shitou rivers to ease urban
water shortage.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Xi'an has simplified its procedures for
establishing overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
Xi'an has 1,212 registered overseas-funded enterprises with a
total investment of three billion US dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
