<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Potential Relations Between China and Latin America: FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- China and Latin America, with
their complementary economies, should strengthen their economic
trade and technological cooperation, Chinese Vice-Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen said here today.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, Qian said China and the Latin
American countries are all developing nations, and have the same
development plans and good bases of cooperation. Although
geographically far apart, exchanges of high-level visits between
China and Latin America have been frequent.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that he talked with foreign ministers of the RIO
Group on six separate occasions during the annual United Nations
General Assembly held in New York City.
</P>
<P>
From January to November this year, the total trade volume
between China and Latin America totaled 6.03 billion US dollars, up
12.6 percent over the same period in 1995, Qian noted.
</P>
<P>
And there have been more exchanges between China and the Latin
American countries which had not previously forged diplomatic ties
with China, Qian said.
</P>
<P>
China and Panama have set up trade development offices in each
other's capital cities, Qian noted, adding that China and Haiti
have reached an agreement to establish a trade cooperation
office.  
</P>
</TEXT>
