<HEADLINE> Shanghai Customs to Start Computerized Tariffs System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai customs
authority and the city's local branch of the Industrial and
Commercial Bank of China recently signed a contract to co-develop
a computerized system for determining tariffs.
</P>
<P>
Trial operation of the system will be carried out in the
Hongqiao Airport customs agency and the Waigaoqiao Bonded Zone.
The system will be applicable to all the other customs in the city
later.
</P>
<P>
With the new system, tariffs on imported goods can be set
directly at the customs office, using electronic data exchanges
with the bank.
</P>
<P>
Importers who formerly had to shuttle between customs and the
bank now need only to provide all the required documentation of
their goods to the customs office. 
</P>
