has spent 300 million yuan launching a data telecommunications
network in order to speed up the modernization of its
telecommunications infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
So far, the network has extended its coverage to all cities,
counties and some economically developed townships across Hebei,
providing such data telecom services as data interchange and frame
relay, according to the "Guangdong-Hong Kong Information Daily."
</P>
<P>
The network, which includes a Internet node in Shijiazhuang,
capital of Hebei, has signed up more than 3,000 regular users.
</P>
<P>
Based on the network, Hebei will build a province-wide super
information highway which will add the digital, broad-band and
intelligent functions to Hebei's telecom system. 
