<HEADLINE> Domestic Switching Systems Enter Beijing's Telephone Web </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Beijing has purchased 24,000
lines of switching gears from a domestic manufacturer, in a bid
to raise the localization rate of its telephone exchange system.
</P>
<P>
The Municipal Telecommunications Administration recently signed
the contract with Huawei Technology Ltd., a leading Chinese
switching machine plant based in Shenzhen, said China Electronics
News.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the 24,000 lines of C&AMP;C 08 switchs, Huawei will
also supply Beijing with a switching center and maintenance
facilities.
</P>
<P>
Ni Yilin, director of the administration, said that the China
has greatly narrowed the gap between its telecommunications
products and foreign ones by increasing technology imports and
improving productivity. "So, it is the time to equip China's
telecom trunks with domestic products," he said.
</P>
<P>
As a potential challenger to foreign switching products, the
Huawei machines are used in a number of Chinese cities including
Tianjin, Guangzhou and Shenzhen.  
</P>
