<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-30 09:28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Labor Federation to Escalate Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The Histadrut, Israeli
Labor Federation, plans to escalate its campaign of selective
strikes in different sectors today, after throwing Israel into
chaos Sunday with wildcat strikes in response to the arrest
of a labor leader.
</P>
<P>
According to an Israel Radio report, airports are to be
spared today, after 60 scheduled flights were disrupted due to
Sunday afternoon's sudden walkout, hot on the heels of a
strike last Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The school system will also be unaffected today, and at 4
p.m. local time (1400GMT) the Histadrut top brass will meet
to decide where the strike action will hit Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Binyamin Netanyahu and Finance Minister Dan
Meridor lashed out at the Histadrut and accused it of
sponsoring a political campaign against the government.
</P>
<P>
The employers urged Netanyahu Sunday night to seek
back-to-work orders and threatened to withhold deductions from
employees' wages which constitute the chief source of income
for the Histadrut.
</P>
<P>
Last week, the Histadrut decided to hold selective strikes
every day, starting last Thursday, to protest the government's
planned budget cuts, as well as its economic policy.
</P>
<P>
However, the spark which ostensibly led to the wildcat
action at midday Sunday was the detention of Histadrut Trade
Union Department Chairman Shlomo Shani, who had gone underground
over the weekend after the Tel Aviv Labor Court ruled him
in contempt.
</P>
<P>
This followed Shani's violation of an order to limit
Thursday's strikes in the ports and railroads system to three
hours, and he was picked up by police after he showed up
at a Haifa Chemicals demonstration, in northern Israel.
</P>
<P>
Histadrut Chairman Amir Peretz immediately ordered employees in
all sectors of the economy to walk out over what he
charged was the first ever attempt in the country to
infringe upon the right to strike.
</P>
<P>
His call was heeded at the Ben-Gurion Airport, where it caused
chaos, at banks, the train system, radio and TV, and several
private plants.
</P>
<P>
This came on top of scheduled strikes by Electric
Cooperation employees, Bezeq, Israel's main communication firm,
and the ports, where the work stoppage is entering its
second week and causing great losses.
</P>
<P>
The wildcat side of the dispute ended some five hours
after it began, when the Tel Aviv Labor Court agreed to
let Shani go. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19961230.0127 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to hold 5th Session of 8th NPC Next March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- A decision to hold the 5th
session of the 8th National People's Congress (NPC) in Beijing
next March was made here today at the closing ceremony of the 23rd
session of the 8th NPC's Standing Committee, China's top
legislature.
</P>
<P>
According to the decision, the agenda of the 5th session of the
8th NPC includes the following items: to hear and deliberate the
government work report; to examine and approve a report on the
enforcement of the Plan for National Economic and Social
Development in 1996; and to examine reports on the enforcement of
state and local budgets of 1996 and on the state budget of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The fifth session of the 8th NPC is scheduled to examine and
discuss the Amendment to the Criminal Law, the draft of the
National Defense Law, and issues concerning the number and
election of deputies to the Ninth National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
A proposal to establish Chongqing, an industrial center in
southwest China's Sichuan Province, into a municipality directly
under the central government, which was submitted by the State
Council, is scheduled to be deliberated during the 5th session of
the 8th NPC.
</P>
<P>
As is customary, the 5th session will also hear, examine and
deliberate work reports by the Standing Committee of the NPC, the
Supreme People's Court and the Supreme People's Procuratorate.
</P>
<P>
The decision says that the 5th session of the 8th NPC is
scheduled to hear and discuss a report on the enforcement of the
Agriculture Law, the first of its kind in China. Experts believe
that law-enforcement inspection, as a means of legal supervision,
has become more mature and will play an increasingly important
role in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
