<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Calls for Bigger Proportion of Female Deputies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The proportion of women
deputies in the National People's Congress (NPC) should be further
increased so as to protect women's political rights and ensure
their equal status with men, some members of the NPC standing
committee urged here today.
</P>
<P>
In a joint statement, they pointed out that since the founding
of the People's Republic in 1949, women's status and rights have
been acknowledged and largely improved. Women are making great
contributions to the nation in every field, they said.
</P>
<P>
However, the proportion of female cadres is still on the low
side, they said, citing that the number of female deputies in the
NPC only account for about 21 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
The statements were made by NPC standing committee member Nie
Li and four other members.
</P>
<P>
They said that although the proportion of women in the NPC
membership ranks the 15th in the world compared with similar
foreign institutions, there are only 19 female members in the
standing committee, making up only about 12 percent of the total
number.
</P>
<P>
The statement pointed out that the amount is not in conformity
with the political rights stipulated in the constitution and laws
that women share the equal rights with men, and it cannot meet
China's advanced social system.
</P>
<P>
As a nationwide campaign is to be launched to elect the new
NPC, the country should adopt necessary measures to ensure that
the proportion of female deputies is higher than that of the
current conference, the committee members maintained.
</P>
<P>
They noted that an increase in the proportion of female
deputies serves as an important means to safeguard the
constitution and law, ensure women can be equal with men, and
realize China's commitment to the international community.
</P>
<P>
They said that the progress of women's rights has provided
conditions for them to participate in state affairs.
</P>
<P>
Since 1949, the opportunities for Chinese women to take part in
politics has been constantly improved. Additionally, since the
adoption of the NPC system 42 years ago, female deputies to the
NPC have played an important role in making laws and managing
social affairs.
</P>
<P>
The proportion of female deputies to the NPC has grown to 21.03
percent compared with 12 percent at the first NPC.
</P>
<P>
These deputies have paid particular attention to the issues of
public health, environment, the protection of the rights of women
and children, social security and culture and ethics, and have put
forward suggestions in these areas.
</P>
<P>
Many important laws were made because of female deputies'
proposals and participation.
</P>
<P>
The five members urged that a temporary special measure be
worked out to ensure that women enjoy equal rights with men, and
that the proportion of female deputies to the next NPC be
increased.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of the NPC and local people's congresses should attach
more importance to the issue, the committee noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
