<HEADLINE> China Appoints new Top Officer of Defense Science and Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The National People's
Congress, China's top legislative body, today approved the
appointment of the new Minister in Charge of the Commission of
Science, Technology and Industry for National Defense.
</P>
<P>
Cao Gangchuan, a 61-year-old lieutenant general, was appointed
to the position by Premier Li Peng six days ago. An announcement
naming the new minister was made at the 23rd Plenum of the
Standing Committee of the Eighth National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
The former top chief of the military scientific and
technological industry, General Ding Henggao, was removed from his
post because he had reached the retirement age limit.
</P>
<P>
Cao, former Deputy Chief of General Staff of the People's
Liberation Army, majored in missile design at the Advanced
Military Engineering School of the Artillery Corps of the former
Soviet Union, from 1957 to 1963.
</P>
<P>
The missile engineer had also been Deputy Director of the
Military Equipment Department of the General Staff Headquarters,
Director of the Military Affairs Department of the General Staff
Headquarters, and Director of the Military Trade Office under the
Central Military Commission.
</P>
<P>
In the appointment proposal endorsed by Premier Li, Cao was
described as being an expert in military equipment, and rich in
experience in military equipment management. 
</P>
