<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 15 Bandits Killed in Attack Against Cattle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen bandits were
reportedly shot dead by Kenyan security force in a counter attack
against armed cattle rustlers in the Suguta Valley in northern
Kenya, The Daily Nation reported today.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted Department of Defense sources as saying that
several AK-47 assault rifles and hundreds of cattles have been
recovered.
</P>
<P>
The security force was now widening their area of operation to
contain escaping of the cattle rustlers to other areas.
</P>
<P>
The security personnel have used 10 helicopters and light
tanks to comb the Suguta Valley and sealed off the whole area of
the valley to cut off any escape routes, the paper added.
</P>
<P>
The operation involves a combined force of the army,
paramilitary General Service Unit, regular and administrative
police.
</P>
<P>
Following the shooting down of an army helicopter by armed
bandits, in which a district commissioner and two army officers
were killed last Thursday, the combined force launched a counter
offensive against the bandits.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that about 600 cattle rustlers were holed up
in the valley which borders the Samburu and Turkana districts in
northern Kenya. 
