<DOCNO> XIE19961230.0144 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangxi People Discover Value of Sky-Blue Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The fortunes of the Beibu Gulf
area in southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region changed
the day that local people cast their eyes out towards the sky-blue
sea.
</P>
<P>
Just a few years ago the thoughts of the locals focussed on the
mountains, rivers and lake areas, and the farmlands. Whenever they
talked about their region they seldom paid any attention to the
beautiful sea bordering their region to the south.
</P>
<P>
The value of the sea was only realized after the central
authorities formed a plan in 1990 to develop the Beibu Gulf area
into the main passage to overseas for southwest China, which is
rich in natural resources.
</P>
<P>
Now the vocabularies of the local people are sprinkled with
words like gold, silver, sea and bay, all reflecting the growing
major tourism zones and buildings in the area.
</P>
<P>
Names like the Silver Beach Tourism Zone in Beihai city, the
Golden Bay Hotel in Qinzhou city, and the Golden Shore Hotel in
Fangcheng port, show distinctively the local people's awareness of
the surrounding sea.
</P>
<P>
Since the change in direction, Guangxi's traditional
industrial structure of focusing on agriculture has been gradually
changed into one spearheaded by the development of its seaports,
and based on the comprehensive development of industry, commerce
and agriculture.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the number of the berths of the three main
ports in the area - Beihai, Fangcheng and Qinzhou - has risen from
ten to 68, handling more than ten million tons of cargo each year.
</P>
<P>
Its economic growth pattern has been shifting towards one
featured by co-operation with overseas businesses.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, the Beibu Gulf area has utilized
overseas investment worth about 1.5 billion US dollars, and more
than 8,000 overseas-funded businesses have been established there.
</P>
<P>
The area has scored an annual GDP growth rate over 20 percent
over the past few years, making it the fastest growing area in
Guangxi and all of southwest China. The sea has proved to be a
gold winner for the region.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
