<HEADLINE> Chinese Enjoy Higher Living Standard </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The living standard of the
Chinese people improved in 1996 with a continued increase in
household incomes, Ye Zhen, spokesman for the State Statistical
Bureau, announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The per-capita living expenses of urban households will
be 4,380 yuan in 1996, a growth of 3.4 percent in real terms, he
said at a press conference today.
</P>
<P>
However, the life of some low-income households remained
difficult, he said.
</P>
<P>
The per-capita net income of rural households will be 1,900
yuan in 1996, a real growth of eight percent, as a result of the
increase in the state purchasing prices of grain and a substantial
increase in grain production, he said. 
