<HEADLINE> China's Agriculture Strengthened </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, December 30 (Xinhua) -- China's grain production will
reach 480 million tons this year, which sets another all-time
high, Ye Zhen, a spokesman for the State Statistics Bureau, said
at a press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
Another bumper harvest was recorded in grain production, and
the shortage in the supply of major farm produce was alleviated.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, the production of cotton and oil-bearing
crops is expected to drop as a result of the decline in sowing
acreage.
</P>
<P>
The annual production of cotton is estimated at four million
tons, down by 800,000 tons from 1995, and that of oil-bearing
crops will be 21.9 million tons, down by 600,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Stable growth was scored in animal husbandry and fisheries, with
annual output of meats and aquatic products growing by about
10 percent, respectively. 
