<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Eight children were wounded
Sunday when a grenade exploded in a mosque in West Java Province
of Indonesia, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The mosque is located in Cibalong District, some 30 kilometers
south of the town of Tasikmalaya where a severe riot took place
last Thursday, said the reports.
</P>
<P>
The children reportedly found the grenade on Saturday in a
trash container near the police station, one of the buildings
which became the targets in Thursday's riots.
</P>
<P>
They took the grenade into the mosque and played with it.
</P>
<P>
The grenade exploded when one of the children pulled its pin
causing a loud bang and destroying mosque windows.
</P>
<P>
The case is now being investigated by the mobile brigade of
West Java police, said the reports.
</P>
<P>
Last Thursday, a riot hit Tasikmalaya, 225 kilometers southeast
of Jakarta, during which four people were killed, 15 others
injured and about 100 buildings and more than 100 cars were
destroyed or burned down.
</P>
<P>
The riot started as a protest by thousands of Muslims against
alleged police mistreatment of three Muslim teachers in the town.
 
