<HEADLINE> Township Enterprise Development in Chaoyang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Township-run enterprises have
become a major part of the local economy and a major source of
local revenues in Chaoyang city, Guangdong province.
</P>
<P>
These enterprises scored a total turnover of 12 billion yuan in
the first nine months of this year, up 32 percent from the same
period in 1995.
</P>
<P>
They paid 280 million yuan in taxes to the local government
last year, 80 percent of Chaoyang revenues from consolidated
industrial and commercial tax.
</P>
<P>
Chaoyang currently has more 10,000 township-run enterprise,
which employ a total of 300,000 people. In the January-October
period in 1996, 180 enterprises each manufactured at least ten
million yuan (1.2 million US dollars) worth-of goods, and ten
enterprises each turned out more than 100 million yuan worth-of
goods.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of this year, 12 groups of rural
enterprises have been launched, bringing the number of such groups
to 29 and the value of their assets to 1.4 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Agriculture has listed 35 rural enterprises in
Chaoyang as major township-run ones in China.
</P>
<P>
So far this year, the Chaoyang city government has held trade
and investment fairs in Thailand, Singapore and the Republic of
Korea. As a result, 12 contracts involving 2.26 billion US dollars
in total investment were signed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
