<DOCNO> XIE19961230.0180 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: South Asia's Poverty Alleviation Gains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, December 30 (Xinhua) -- South Asia, where nearly
half of the world's poor people live, enhanced its
poverty-fighting efforts in 1996 by emphasizing social
mobilization and local people's involvement.
</P>
<P>
The year saw a new model project of poverty alleviation in the
region aimed at encouraging local participation and strengthening
coordination in the field among South Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
The region, where more than 400 million people live in
destitution, is also a priority area on the poverty alleviation
agenda of the U.N. Development Program (UNDP), which launched a
full-scale poverty alleviation program in South Asia this year to
help fulfill the region's commitment to eradicating poverty by
2002.
</P>
<P>
Actually, the region's joint effort to overcome poverty started
in 1994, when its leaders met at a summit of the South Asian
Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC) in Dhaka, Bangladesh,
and adopted a declaration pledging to eradicate poverty in the
region preferably by the year 2002.
</P>
<P>
Governments of the seven SAARC member countries -- Bangladesh,
Bhutan, India, the Maldives, Nepal, Pakistan and Sri Lanka --
later reaffirmed their commitment to fighting against rampant
poverty by declaring 1995 as the "SAARC Year of Poverty
Eradication."
</P>
<P>
With the support of the Economic and Social Commission for Asia
and the Pacific (ESCAP) and the UNDP, the SAARC launched last June
a project called "SAARC Seven Sisters" with a view to contributing
to member countries' poverty-fighting efforts.
</P>
<P>
The project, launched as a follow-up to the past poverty
alleviation activities, selected six districts, one in each of the
seven SAARC countries excluding Bhutan, as models for improving
local organizations' involvement in poverty-fighting programs.
</P>
<P>
It also proposed the establishment of district-level forums in
these model districts on a trial basis to bring together all
parties involved in local poverty alleviation.
</P>
<P>
A sub-regional networking of these district-level forums is
expected under the project for sharing experiences and exchanging
information on poverty alleviation among the participating
countries, according to sources of the SAARC Secretariat in
Kathmandu.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the UNDP renewed its poverty alleviation
program in South Asia this year by providing a package assistance
of 1.3 million U.S. dollars to support the implementation of the
Dhaka Declaration on poverty eradication.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in 1994, the UNDP launched the South Asia Poverty
Alleviation Program with 800,000 dollars to provide the poor with
credit opportunities for income generation and skill development
in cooperation with the governments in the region.
</P>
<P>
A large number of people in South Asia, especially those living
in poverty-stricken rural areas, have benefited from these poverty
alleviation initiatives, SAARC officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19961230.0181 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Special Economic Zone Becomes Video Recorder Exporter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Xiamen, a special economic zone
in Southeast China's Fujian Province, has exported 3,500 video
cassette recorders to the Philippines. The deal signals the
beginning of its role as an emerging electronics supplier for
global markets.
</P>
<P>
The 3,500 VCRs manufactured by the Xiaxin Company Ltd., the
first joint venture established in Xiamen in 1985, passed a
quality appraisal by the Ministry of Electronics Industry last
April, and has proved to be of the same technical benchmark as
western products.
</P>
<P>
During the past eight months, Xiaxin had put seven VCR brands
onto the domestic markets, and sold 100,000 machines. Its products
are now the third best seller after Japanese-made Panasonic VCRs
and products by Samsung of the Republic of Korea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
