<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Foreign Trade Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- China will handle imports and
exports totaling 290 billion US dollars in 1996, an increase of
3.3 percent over 1995.
</P>
<P>
Of the figure, exports will come to 153 billion US dollars, up
by three percent, and imports, 137 billion dollars, a four percent
rise, with a trade surplus of 16 billion US dollars, Ye Zhen,
spokesman for the State Statistics Bureau, announced at a news
conference here today.
</P>
<P>
A total of 48 billion US dollars worth of foreign funds were
actually utilized in 1996, with direct foreign investment
amounting to 40 billion dollars, up by seven percent over the last
year.
</P>
<P>
China's foreign exchange reserves for the whole of 1996 are
expected to exceed 100 billion US dollars, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
