<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Firms Punished for Violating Custom Rules </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Customs Office
has punished three foreign trade companies for violating
regulations on the duty security system.
</P>
<P>
They are the first punishments made by customs since the
adoption of the off-the-balance accounting system on foreign trade
processors, according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
The three enterprises, involved in garments, electrical and
machine factories, had imported chemical fabrics, electric motors
and batteries worth 250,000 US dollars, and had failed to
re-export the items on time.
</P>
<P>
In line with State Council regulations, Shanghai Customs issued
notices to stop the use of accounts opened by the three
firms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
