<HEADLINE> Thoma Wins World Cup Ski Jumping Event </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 29 (Xinhua) -- German Dieter Thoma won the World
Cup ski jumping event in Obertsdorf, Germany on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
With 253 points, Thoma finished ahead of Norway's Kristian
Brenden, who was second with 252.6 points. Austria's Andreas
Goldberger was third with 246.7.
</P>
<P>
Primoz Peterka of Slovenia, who leads in the World Cup
standings, finished seventh with 233.7 points. Brenden and Thoma
follow him in the overall standings.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's was the ninth World Cup victory for the 27-year-old
Thoma and put him in the lead in the four-jump tournament, which
he won in 1989-90.
</P>
<P>
The four-jump tournament continues New Year's Day in
Garmisch-Partenkirschen, then moves to Austria for the final two
events. 
</P>
