<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guatemalan Government, Guerrillas Sign  Accord to End </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUATEMALA CITY, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Guatemala's government
and the guerrillas today signed here an accord to end the
country's 36-year war, the longest in Central America.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by leaders of the Guatemalan National
Liberation Unit (URNG) guerrillas and government peace negotiators.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony was attended by President Alvaro Arzu, outgoing
U.N. Secretary-General Boutros Boutros-Ghali, and leaders from
many Latin American countries and Spain.
</P>
<P>
The 36-year war in the country has left more than 140,000
people dead. 
</P>
</TEXT>
